OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDaily Mail: Geordie Greig  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fstepping down as editor    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Geordie Greig is stepping down as      
OL,6, editor of the Daily Mail after three   
OL,7, years in the role.                     
OL,9,FHe will be replaced by Ted Verity, the 
OL,10,Fcurrent editor of the Mail on Sunday,  
OL,11,Fwho will have overall responsibility   
OL,12,Ffor both papers.                       
OL,14,FAnnouncing the move, Lord Rothermere,  
OL,15,Fchairman of the Mail's owner DMGT, said
OL,16,FGreig had been "outstanding".          
OL,18,FGreig - who will now become a          
OL,19,Fconsultant editor - wished the         
OL,20,Fnewspaper "continued good fortune".    
